subproject.description:
Establish Good Poultry Health and Production Programmes in 4 pilot provinces over a 9 month period. 
•	To support the development of an economically strong poultry sub-sector, both to strengthen rural livelihoods and as the most effective means of improving standards in public and veterinary health;
•	To combine animal health and animal production sectors through a risk-based approach to disease control;
•	Strengthen Province-level planning and decision making and foster linkages between Provincial offices and technical advices
•	Strengthen public and private sector collaboration in poultry production and health management;
•	Ensure that development of the poultry sub-sector does not result in environmental degradation; and
•	Build on existing outputs from the  Joint Programme and other projects.

